# Normalize line endings to LF for all text files so the repo is consistent across
# platforms and matches .editorconfig and the Linux CI. Binary files are auto-detected.
* text=auto eol=lf

# ...except Windows batch files, which cmd.exe must receive as CRLF. This is not cosmetic:
# under the blanket eol=lf above, cmd tolerates LF for plain sequential lines but MIS-PARSES
# `for /f` loops and parenthesized `if (...)` blocks - it runs REM lines as commands and
# expands %VARS% set inside them to nothing. "Start CPU Visualizer.bat" needs both constructs
# to reuse a running dev server, so with LF it silently fails open and starts a duplicate
# server instead. The old launcher survived on LF only because its single block (the
# node_modules install) is skipped whenever node_modules already exists.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# Explicit binaries (none yet, but keep the convention obvious for future assets).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
